The local government has decided to oppose this unusual “social measure”.
He issued an information leaflet that should help avoid witch hunts.
However, this has a glue.
“More than 70% of adults in Burkina Faso don’t know how to read,” warns Die Standard newspaper about the disadvantages of written awareness.
Accusations of witchcraft are also common in other African countries.
