More and more parents are using people’s tracking devices to control their children.
Fear of children leads more and more people to think about controlling them by GPS.
The system, initially designed for vehicle tracking, can also follow the movement of people and thus contribute, for example, in case of the disappearance of the nine-year-old girl Ani<0xC4><0x8D>ka Janatkov<0xC3><0xA1>.
For the moment, the device has the approximate size of a watch case, but it will soon be reduced to the size of a watch.
Many people feared the case of the missing Ani<0xC4><0x8D>ka and began to report on the available means to better protect their children.
Even at the cost of invading your privacy.
“We are all trying to tell ourselves that this is not about spying, but another way to reduce the chances of a tragedy,” said Petr Pilin of Macro Weil, one of the providers of tracking devices in the Czech market.
“I recognize that in certain cases such devices can be abused, for example if they are put in someone’s pocket without their knowledge, but we have not yet encountered such cases.”
“Most customers really buy it for security reasons,” adds Pilin.
In their opinion, children should always know what the "cajita" is for and how it is used in an emergency.
Child psychologist Dana Bo<0xC4><0x8D>kov<0xC3><0xA1> warns about the fact that if the child does not want to carry it, he will simply throw it away.
“Even the youngest children show great creativity when it comes to intentionally losing certain things if they want to avoid being controlled.”
“In the past, parents relied heavily on mobile phones, but these could be turned off as easily as the tracking device,” says Bo<0xC4><0x8D>kov<0xC3><0xA1>.
In his opinion, it is questionable whether in the event of an attack such a device is really useful.
“If it’s a prepared kidnapping, the author will almost always check if the child is carrying some kind of electronic device that can reveal their location.”
"It's the phone now."
“As the use of tracking devices goes on, you will also look for them, as their sale will certainly be done with a lot of advertising.”
“In such cases, criminals always go one step ahead of the police,” says the psychologist.
However, he adds that such devices can help in the case of an impromptu attack by a pedophile.
According to Robert <0xC4><0x8C>ech of the company RC Monitoring, which offers tracking services for both vehicles and people, even in the event that, after an attack, the tracking device is immediately destroyed, its presence can serve as a help.
"The device can be configured to regularly send the position after a certain period."
"If it suffers damage, it will at least facilitate the last position of the person in question."
“The most expensive devices have an inclination meter integrated, so if the person simply slips and remains motionless, the device will immediately issue a warning with the position in question,” says <0xC4><0x8C>ech.
In his opinion, such a service can be obtained even with smartphones with navigation, in which only special software should be installed.
The problem with current tracking units is that at the moment they are devices with a similar size to a slingshot box or smaller mobile phones.
