Just for comparison: the annual mecha consumption of the pyrotechnics of the police, who eliminate the ammunition of the Second World War or that left by the Soviet army, does not exceed 1,500 meters for years.
In addition, the police always ask only for the right amount to deplete the ammunition before its useful life is over.
They decided it for safety reasons for pyrotechnics and, in the meantime, more modern and reliable types of wicking can be obtained.
The Ministry already has clear difficulties in finishing tens of thousands of tons of ammunition from the time of the Warsaw Pact, when the Czechoslovak army of two hundred thousand people was preparing for a campaign in the Rhine.
According to the pyrotechnics with whom MF DNES spoke, after a couple of years the following problem will occur with the current: it will have to eliminate hundreds of kilometers of old mecha, which is now being bought "bad".
