Young Czechs get drunk with Fernet and rum. The beer is no longer in fashion, because it takes effect slowly
Fernet, rum, vodka and even good whiskeys stolen from their parents.
These are the beverages that cause young drinkers under the age of fifteen to end up in medical care.
Children who end up lying in the hospital continuously to overcome the relapse are no longer an exception.
This is derived from the experience of doctors who encounter such cases in hospital pediatric admissions.
"Drinking beer or wine is no longer fashionable, because it takes a long time to drink them."
