"He was at the Hole<0xC5><0xA1>ovice fair at some dance party."
“The interesting thing is that his mother wasn’t surprised that his daughter disappeared for 48 hours,” he said.
It is precisely the lack of interest of parents or even their clear tolerance for drinking on the part of their children that is considered the main cause of the increase in alcohol consumption among young people.
Experts point out that, in the case of children, it is not possible to speak properly of dependence.
“An alcoholic is a person who has been chronically addicted to alcohol for several years, with all the phenomena associated with it, which does not occur in children.”
“In those who drink alcohol repeatedly, it is rather due to a systematically failed social or family environment,” Pelik<0xC3><0xA1>n explains.
According to spokeswoman Jurinov<0xC3><0xA1>, up until mid-November 40 drunk children were hospitalized at the Motol pediatric clinic this year.
However, statistics show only those who come with serious poisoning and should remain in the hospital.
Young drinkers who, after ambulatory medical recognition, go home with their parents or with the police, do not count.
In addition to the cases in which the children simply meet after school and drink booze, for Pelik<0xC3><0xA1>n there are three seasonal ups and downs to mention: the day of witches, the end of the year and the end of the school year.
"In such a circumstance, they drink from bad grades or, on the contrary, celebrate the beginning of the holidays."
“On the day of the witches I have come to see in admissions up to seven drunk children at a time,” adds Pelik<0xC3><0xA1>n.
Drinkers who spend the night in detox under the supervision of doctors, paradoxically, have the advantage that the next day they do not suffer a terrible relapse at home.
Morning headaches, caused by dehydration and glucose deficiency, are avoided by injecting a serum with glucose and with nutrients that the body lacks.
"These take it much better, because after the hectic night, they get up well and they don't hurt anything."
“They only show confusion about where they are,” Pelik<0xC3><0xA1>n says, adding that patients often lose their good mood at least when they see the expenses they have generated.
The transfer in an ambulance and hospitalization in a room for serious patients costs about tens of thousands of crowns.
“I have often used the cost as a means of educating them, when in the visit I tell the children directly how much their intoxication has cost and that they would have to spend the entire summer in a job for young people so that you earn enough to pay for that night,” Pelik<0xC3><0xA1>n adds.
