Then comes the temperament "and inner qualities".
The female Chengguan are like florists, he said, and added, "in addition to being florists, they will have other responsibilities."
Zheng Lihua, deputy director of the district’s city administration office, is not eager to support that description.
But he noted that height requirements were standard in many Chinese job notices for both sexes.
Then comes the need for harmonious facial features.
