“We can’t allow a person to pick up or a squirrel to come to work here,” Mr. Zheng said.
"His image would not be good."
Liu Yi, who patrols Baoguang Square near a monastery, is 22 years old, with his cheeks colored and a subtly curved mouth.
She doesn’t think the accent in her appearance is sexist, she said.
