This prepared the ground for Wednesday's deal to remove the rest of the material, about 227 kg, according to an official, who spoke from anonymity due to the confidentiality of the matter.
The agreement appeared to be one of the most important outcomes of the 47-nation Nuclear Security Summit chaired by Obama in April, which excluded Belarus.
