I hope that the current turbulence will leave room for more tranquility.
And let us take advantage of the window of opportunity that they have given us, until the spring of 2013.
It seems that President Zapatero has also understood this, and his dual manifesto (the reforms promised after last Saturday’s meeting with big companies and yesterday’s announcement of new measures) suggests that, despite criticism of Merkel, the thesis that we have to put order at home has opened up.
But the red line that Germany has drawn there is, and it doesn’t look like they’re going to move it.
And, among the possibilities envisaged, that of leaving a monetary zone too crowded with less serious countries, cannot be excluded.
